reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great accessories for the car cabin
reviews.reviewText: The JUSTTOP Car Trash Can is an essential accessory for anyone looking to keep their car cabin neat and tidy. This small, automatic, and portable trash can with its elegant diamond design not only serves its purpose but also adds a touch of style to the car’s interior.What I found most beneficial about this trash can is its convenience and utility. It’s the perfect size for a car, easily fitting in a variety of spaces without taking up too much room. The automatic lid is a smart feature, making it effortless to dispose of trash, especially while driving. This design ensures that the cabin remains clean and free from small litter that can often accumulate during journeys.The ease of cleaning this trash can is another plus. It’s simple to maintain and keeps looking as good as new with minimal effort. Additionally, its versatility extends beyond the car – it’s suitable for use in the home or office too, making it a multipurpose item.The black color and diamond design give it a premium look, which is a nice departure from the usual bland car accessories. It blends well with the car’s interior, and the lid ensures that the trash is out of sight, helping maintain an overall neat appearance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very discreet, sleek, and so handy to have in the car!
reviews.reviewText: I get compliments on these all the time!! I love that it is so easy to keep my car clutter free and they fit perfectly into the door cup holders. Empty them out when you get gas, they are very easy to wash if needed and passengers won't be hiding tissues and napkins on their side! They have held up great, spring mechanism did come apart once, but it was so easy to put it back together. No issues, would 10 out of 10 buy again if I lose any.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sleek, and practical.
reviews.reviewText: Does not fit in the pocket of my side door (I drive a GMC terrain), but it fits perfectly in the cup holder. I use it everyday, and it comes in handy for small pieces of trash, like straws, napkins, etc. Keeps my car neat, I love it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought this back in 11/22 and the spring assembly on the lid kicked the bed today. But it was $8 and it’s honestly a great little contraption. I’m happily buying a replacement. The can fits perfectly in the driver-side door of my 2017 Subaru Impreza Hatchback. I prefer it there in lieu of the cup holder from a look standpoint. I like for my car to be clutter free and this blends right in with the door. The receptacle fills up quick if you’re throwing out fast food receipts, sticky notes, etc. but this holds a ton of straw wrappers.For $8 it’s a very fair deal. Yes, it’s rather cheaply made, but there really shouldn’t be a whole lot of rough and tumble with it anyways. It should just sit in the cup holder/preferred spot, and it’ll be fine. I plan to repurpose the broken one as a “penny jar” in the cupboard. I just wanted one with a working lid for the car.It’s silly to like a garbage can for cars so much, but it really does encourage me to keep my car clean, and it’s nice to have on long haul car rides.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Almost what I was looking for
reviews.reviewText: I like that these are not huge, they stand upright, and have lids that automatically close due to a spring. My biggest issue is that the lids do not stay on very well (they pop off so easily) and sometimes if they fall off from my center console and hit the car floor at a weird angle, the spring pin comes out and I have to put the whole thing back together. It’s not a huge deal, but it’s annoying and just needs to be a little sturdier.I also wish they came in different sizes because these are just too big for the lower “pocket” in my car doors.
